Question 1: Determine Optimal k (Full Data)

Using silhouette score to find optimal k with K-means and hierarchical clustering.

K-Means on Full Data

In[127]:
# Calculate Silhouette Score for K-means with different k values (Full Data)
k_range = range(2, 11)
silhouette_scores_kmeans_full = []

print("K-Means Clustering on Full Data (10 variables)")
print("=" * 60)

for k in k_range:
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42, n_init=10)
    labels = kmeans.fit_predict(X_scaled)
    sil_score = silhouette_score(X_scaled, labels)
    silhouette_scores_kmeans_full.append(sil_score)
    print(f"k={k}: Silhouette Score = {sil_score:.4f}")

# Find optimal k
optimal_k_kmeans_full = k_range[np.argmax(silhouette_scores_kmeans_full)]
optimal_sil_kmeans_full = max(silhouette_scores_kmeans_full)

print(f"\nOptimal k for K-means (Full Data): k = {optimal_k_kmeans_full}")
print(f"Best Silhouette Score: {optimal_sil_kmeans_full:.4f}")

In[129]:
# Calculate Silhouette Score for Hierarchical clustering with Average linkage (Full Data)
from scipy.cluster.hierarchy import fcluster

silhouette_scores_hier_full = []

print("\nHierarchical Clustering with Average Linkage on Full Data (10 variables)")
print("=" * 60)

# Compute linkage matrix with average method
linkage_matrix_avg = linkage(X_scaled, method='average')

for k in k_range:
    labels = fcluster(linkage_matrix_avg, k, criterion='maxclust')
    sil_score = silhouette_score(X_scaled, labels)
    silhouette_scores_hier_full.append(sil_score)
    print(f"k={k}: Silhouette Score = {sil_score:.4f}")

# Find optimal k
optimal_k_hier_full = k_range[np.argmax(silhouette_scores_hier_full)]
optimal_sil_hier_full = max(silhouette_scores_hier_full)

print(f"\nOptimal k for Hierarchical (Full Data): k = {optimal_k_hier_full}")
print(f"Best Silhouette Score: {optimal_sil_hier_full:.4f}")

Question 2: PCA Dimensionality Reduction

Finding how many principal components are needed for >75% variance.

In[132]:
# Apply PCA for visualization
pca = PCA()
X_pca = pca.fit_transform(X_scaled)

# Explained variance
explained_var = pca.explained_variance_ratio_
cumulative_var = np.cumsum(explained_var)

print("Explained variance by each component:")
for i, var in enumerate(explained_var, 1):
    print(f"PC{i}: {var:.4f} ({var*100:.2f}%)")

print(f"\nCumulative variance explained by first 2 PCs: {cumulative_var[1]:.4f} ({cumulative_var[1]*100:.2f}%)")
print(f"Cumulative variance explained by first 3 PCs: {cumulative_var[2]:.4f} ({cumulative_var[2]*100:.2f}%)")

In[135]:
# Find number of components needed for >75% variance
threshold = 0.75
n_components_75 = np.argmax(cumulative_var >= threshold) + 1

print(f"Components needed for >{threshold*100}% variance: {n_components_75}")
print(f"Cumulative variance with {n_components_75} PCs: {cumulative_var[n_components_75-1]:.4f} ({cumulative_var[n_components_75-1]*100:.2f}%)")

print(f"\nVariance by component:")
for i in range(n_components_75):
    print(f"  PC{i+1}: {explained_var[i]:.4f} ({explained_var[i]*100:.2f}%)")

# Create reduced dataset
X_pca_reduced = X_pca[:, :n_components_75]
print(f"\nReduced data shape: {X_pca_reduced.shape}")

print(f"Full Data    - K-Means: k={optimal_k_kmeans_full} (sil={optimal_sil_kmeans_full:.4f}), Hierarchical: k={optimal_k_hier_full} (sil={optimal_sil_hier_full:.4f})")
print(f"Reduced Data - K-Means: k={optimal_k_kmeans_reduced} (sil={optimal_sil_kmeans_reduced:.4f}), Hierarchical: k={optimal_k_hier_reduced} (sil={optimal_sil_hier_reduced:.4f})")
